'''''Star Wars Insider'' 92''' is the ninety-second issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', released on [[February 19]], [[2007]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"Letters From the Editor"
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*"[[Skywalking]]"
**"[[Refresher Reading]]: 20 Things You Didn't Know About the Massassi Temples" {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; A Fairy Tale Wrapped Around a Fairy Tale {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars: 30th Anniversary Collection|Bookshelf Bragging]] {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" &mdash; No Reward Is Worth This
*"[[Set Piece|Technical Readout]]" &mdash; {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" &mdash; The Bane of Continuity {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Beware of Holy Grails and Fixations! {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[International Collecting|Star Wars International]]" &mdash; The Toys From Brazil {{C|by [[Gus Lopez]]}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" &mdash; Holy Grails: The Unproduced ''Empire'' Micro Collection Line
*"[[Padawan's Corner|Padawan Corner]]" &mdash; How to Draw Admiral Ackbar {{C|by [[Robin Pronovost]]}}
*[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 23

===Features===
*"[[The In-Between Theory]]: Reality Becomes Fantasy in the ''Star Wars'' Photography of Cédric Delsaux" {{C|by [[Patrice Girod]]}}
*:<small>An interview with French photographer [[Cédric Delsaux]] about his visually rich and imaginatively compelling "''Star Wars on Earth" artwork.</small>
*"[[The Toys That Never Were]]" {{C|by [[Chris Fawcett]]}}
*:<small>''Insider'' looks at vintage Kenner figures that were never produced, from the famous missile-firing Boba Fettand vac-metalized figures to an alternate Jedi Luke Skywalker, and unproduced ''Droids'' figures.</small>
*"[[Unknown Origins]]" {{C|by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler|J.W. Rinzler]]}}
*:<small>Lucasfilm's J.W. Rinzler discovers characters, plotlines and other elements that were discarded from early drafts of ''A New Hope'', but later resurfaced in the prequel trilogy.</small>
*"[[Pirates of the Boards]], Part 2"
*:<small>In the second of a six-part series, [[Joe Johnston]]'s never-before-seen storyboards from an early draft of the original ''Star Wars''.</small>
*"[[The Models of Revenge of the Sith|Puzzle Planet: ''The Models of Revenge of the Sith'', Part III]]" {{C|by [[Frank Parisi]]}}
*:<small>In the final installment of a three-part series, [[Brian Gernand]], head of ILM's model shop for Episodes II and III, details how he and his team created the sinkhole world of Utapau.</small>

